      <h2>Lynx Details</h2>
      <ul style="text-align: center; margin-left: 14.5%; background-color: gray;">
        <li>Size – Medium</li><br>
        <li>Weight/build – Muscular, lean</li><br>
        <li>Height/length – Compact body, relatively short tail</li><br>
        <li>Color/pattern – Tawny to gray coat with dark spots</li><br>
        <li>Fur/skin/covering – Thick, furry, with ear tufts</li><br>
        <li>Texture – Soft and dense, silky in winter</li><br>
        <li>Shape/form – Angular frame, long legs, broad paws</li><br>
        <li>Movement style – Graceful, silent stalker, powerful leaper</li><br>
        <li>Posture – Upright when alert, crouched when hunting</li><br>
        <li>Sound/vocalization – Quiet, occasional growls or yowls</li><br>
        <li>Behavior/temperament – Solitary, territorial, elusive</li><br>
        <li>Diet type – Carnivorous (hares, deer, birds, rodents)</li><br>
        <li>Habitat link – Terrestrial, forest and mountain-dwelling</li><br>
        <li>Special traits – Nocturnal, camouflaging coat, snowshoe-like paws</li><br>
        <li>Lifespan/longevity – Long-lived for a wildcat (10–15 years in wild, longer in captivity)</li><br>
        <li>Senses – Keen eyesight, sharp hearing, sensitive smell</li>
      </ul>
